e meat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 So how did you feel your employer treated you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Very well indeed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 How did you feel about him?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 He was one of the best.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 How did you feel about the work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Oh I liked it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 You knew all about it didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 You stayed there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Fifty-four year altogether. I remember this quite well. The - peace celebration lunch.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 You were called up, you went to the war didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Oh yes. I was - at the peace celebration, we had - lunch - had lunch at Market on the Thorpe.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Who could go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 
Oh, ex-service. Only old - soldiers you see. Yes, I marched - we marched from the forest down Mansfield Road and into the Market and had lunch there. The peace celebration, everybody was closed. And - they went round from there round the country.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Would you have preferred another type of occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 When did you decide you wanted to do this sort of job, very early on in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 No, when I was at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Did your parents have much sort of say in what you should do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 No. My father wanted me to take on his trade you see. But I didn't want it. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Did you belong to any trade union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Nothing suitable was there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Did you feel that the employers and workers had the same interests or different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Oh the same I think. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 This was obviously very special wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Yes. We all worked together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Did you feel that there were divisions of interest among workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Some people say that in those days there was a great division between trained craftsmen and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12746636\charrsid8982218 other workers}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 , did you feel that or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12746636\charrsid8982218 Well no, it - it - he would have stopped it, Mr Jessup would have stopped that. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 YES.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 How old is that firm altogether?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 It was established - in 1804. In - you know - next to the Old Black Boy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Did anyone outside the home help your mother look after her house or family, she did it all herself did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Did your sister help much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 She helped with her mother, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 If your mother was ill or confined to bed how did she manage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 She wasn't confined to bed, only at the latter part.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 So if she was ill how did she cope?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Well of course - my sister was there you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Did either of your parents have any relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Yes, father had a - he was born at Osgoddy - Osgoddy. And he had a sister lived at Market Rasen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 How much did they see of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Oh not a great deal.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Did your parents have friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 They were - they were known in the village, everybody knew them, they were - she was born there you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Did they see their friends much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Oh yes, they knew everybody in the village you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Where did they see them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Oh - all over the place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Did they share the same friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Well - in a village they're nearly all friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Did your mother have any friends of her own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Not that I know of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Were friends ever invited into the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Well they used to come in when they wanted anything, you know. Any - anything need doing you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 How often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Oh - it varied.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Would they be offered anything to eat or drink if they came in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 It depends what time of the day it was. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 So they would have been if it was a suitable time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 What sort of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Well, have a cup of tea or anything like that you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Would they be invited in on any special day or occasions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Well - there's no special occasion in those days. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Were friends ever special invited in as opposed to just dropping in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Oh no, there was no special - it was come any time any - near any house you went to. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 So friends called in quite casually without any invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Did neighbours come in casually without invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Do you separate friends and neighbours or were they the same thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 No. All the same. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Did your parents ever go out to visit friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Not very - only into the village, it was - it was four mile from a station you see. There wasn't a - there wasn't the conveyance then.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 People often tell us that in those days they made their own amusements, what do you think your parents did when they got together with the
ir friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Well - talk and suchlike.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Any music at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 
Well - father used to play the violin and - and he was - very - fond of any instrument. He was the first cornet player in the band - in the band there for years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Did your father ever play the violin for dancing or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 
Many people divide society into different social classes or groups, in that time before 1918 did you in the village think of some people belonging to one and some to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 No, they were all - they were all about the same. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Which class or group would you say you belonged to yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 I don't know. We're all in one really. No special groups.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 What sort of people belonged to the same sort of class or group as yourself in the village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Well - no class or anything like that. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 You can't put them into groups at all for me in the village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Your father was very skilled so he was quite high up wasn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Yes, but they a
ll mixed up with one another. No, they didn't sort one another out. Farm labourers used to be in the shop with him as well as anybody else. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Would your parents have been shocked if your sister had married a farm labourer instead of a farmer for instance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 No. Wouldn't have bothered them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Can you remember in the village being taught to touch your cap to anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Well - any ladies or anything like those - touch your cap to 'em. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Did you show your respect in some way? Any other way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 I don't know really as far as I know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Was there anyone you called sir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Well - the squire of the village, we would call him sir or the - the vicar or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Anyone you called master?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 When you were living in the shop did you have to call the shop owner anything special in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 No, not specially.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Do you remember anyone showing respect to your parents in these ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Don't know of any special - all - they were all one with another you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 In the village who were considered the most important people? You mentioned the squire, did he live in the village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 
Yes. He had a - had a fine house in the village. Well it was Manor. He was the - one of them was a magistrate in London. Yes. He - he was a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12746636\charrsid8982218 descendant}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218  of the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12746636\charrsid8982218 Tennyson}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218  the poet you know. Sir }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12746636\charrsid8982218 Tennyson}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218  Acort. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3688485\charrsid8982218 D\rquote Eyncourt}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 
. He was the squire of the village.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Did he live in London some of the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Oh yes, some of the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Was he mostly in the village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Very often in the village, 'course he spent a lot of time in London you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Did you come into contact with him much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Oh yes, often met him in the road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Was he quite friendly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 
Oh yes. Yes, he had - in the - in his park we had. Had a great big park. He had a - a cricket ground and a football ground, and - he used to come when we were playing and - have a game with us sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Did the squire change during the time you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Who else was considered important in the village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 I don't know as anybody else was important as you would say. The vicar and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3688485\charrsid8982218 
that}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Why were these people considered important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Well I don't know the - they'd evidently money there and - one thing and another you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Did the squire own a lot of land, was he a very big landowner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Oh yes - a big landowner.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Who did the shopkeepers associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Any - anybody. There was no - no special group you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 And the clergy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 And teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 And farmers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 What sort of people would you say went to church in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Well - there's three chap
el - there was two chapels in the village - three chapels in the village and a church. So - yes, three chapels when I was there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 You were Wesleyan?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Yes. The Wesleyan, the Primitive. And the - Methodist.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 And the church as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Which sort of people would you say went to which?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 
Oh well - any, there was no special - no. No. Oh there was no divisions there. Some were - some used to go to church, some chapel and - they were all mixed up afterwards. They were good friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Where you lived did all the people in the working class have the same standard of living or would you say there were different groups?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Oh I don't know we had different groups.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Were there different groups economically or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Did you think that one group felt itself superior to the rest in any way?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Were some families thought of as rough and others as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Well one or two - fairly rough ones, but they all mixed up. Yes. They didn't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 What was special about the one or two who were rough, was it the sort of people they were or how they'd been brought up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 How they'd been brought up I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Do you remember a distinction of this kind between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 No, no distinction.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Did your mother and father have the same attitude as each other to people in different groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Oh yes, they - yes, they mixed up one with another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 This didn't come into it much in the village did it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 No. Not a bit, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a particular social group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 No, I don't think so, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Can you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Well I think - Tennyson d'Enycourt was the one as -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Why do you think he was, what was special about him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Well he was a - I don't know how to explain. He'd mix in with people as well as the next you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Can you remember anyone being described as a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Well - his wife, she was a real lady but - she - her mother was Lady Godstone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Do you remember seeing a policeman around where you lived as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Oh yes, one in the village.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 What did you think of him?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Well he was - he was me friend, have a game with us or anything. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 When you were naughty did your mother ever say I'll call the policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 How did you think he treated people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Very well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Was your home in the village rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Did you see anything of the landlord, was he the squire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Well he was the grocer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Did you see much of him then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Yes. I - just before I left school I used to work there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 What were you doing for him then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Oh - odd jobs just in the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 What did you feel about him as a landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Oh, very good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Do you remember feeling that your parents had a struggle to make ends meet ever?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 No, they always - always had plenty to eat and like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Was he ever ill or out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 No. Not until - not until he broke up altogether and died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Did you ever know anyone who had help from the Guardians or the Parish or any charity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 No. No, well you see I left - I left there as soon as I was sixteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 When there was someone in the district who people disapproved of very strongly was there any special way in which they showed it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 You said you had to know their addresses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Why were they considered important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Well - they'd be big land owners wouldn't they. And - Sir Thomas Perkin and Lady Perkin, they're lace people you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11629161 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 
When you came to Nottingham did you think the people in the working class had the same standards of living or would you say there were different groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4396391 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9441483\charrsid8982218 Well I don't now about different groups, we'll say as - the rich and the poor as you may say. Yes.
